title: Testy Butter Bread
details: Brioche is a common type of butter bread, but bakers from various cultures worldwide have their own versions. For example, butterzopf is a butter bread eaten for Sunday breakfast in parts of Switzerland. Dinner rolls are typically a form of butter bread, so are challah, French pain de mie, and German stollen.The comparatively high volume of fat in this type of bread adds sweetness. The fat also makes the bread dough tender and shortens.
